========================================================================

S 2.1  AUTHORSHIP AND ORIGINALITY. I, Elad David Levi -- known also
under the name and designation IACONOUS WORTHYSON -- being the author
and originator of the Works named in the Certificate of Issuance above,
declare that the Works are my own original creation, and that they have
not been copied, stolen, plagiarized, or otherwise misappropriated from
any other person or entity.

S 2.2  PUBLIC-DOMAIN WAIVER, SUBORDINATE TO THIS LICENSE. To the extent
I hold any copyright or neighboring right in the Works beyond what is
expressly governed by this License, I irrevocably waive, abandon, and
dedicate that residual right to the public domain, worldwide, for the
full term of such rights, in the spirit and intent of the Creative
Commons CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication. This waiver does
not diminish, narrow, or contradict the rights, restrictions, and
reservations expressly retained and asserted elsewhere in this License
-- including the eligibility restriction of Article III and the patent
shield of Article V. Where the two could be read in conflict, the
specific operative terms of this License control, and this waiver
operates only as to whatever residue of rights this License does not
itself address.

S 2.3  DEFENSIVE PUBLICATION AS PRIOR ART. Consistent with Article I,
the Works, together with this instrument, are publicly and irrevocably
disclosed as prior art, with the express intent that the ideas,
methods, and designs described herein enter the state of the art, so
that no person or entity may lawfully claim, patent, or otherwise
assert exclusive ownership over them on the basis of having originated
them.

S 2.4  IRREVOCABILITY AND FREE EXPRESSION. This declaration, and the
public disclosure of the Works, are made pursuant to, and in exercise
of, my rights to free expression under applicable law, and are intended
by me to be permanent and irrevocable once published. I do not consent
to, and reserve no right to compel, the suppression, retraction, or
removal of this disclosure. This Section states solely my own
irrevocable intent and consent as author, and does not purport to limit
or override the independent legal rights or obligations of any third
party or hosting platform.

S 2.5  NO CONFLICT WITH THE GRANT. This Article is a personal
declaration of the license holder. It does not affect, narrow, or
expand who may use the Works or how -- that question is governed
exclusively by Article III. A public, irrevocable disclosure of the
Works as prior art is not an invitation for excluded entities to use
them; it is a statement that no one, including an excluded entity, may
patent them.

S 2.6  HONESTY OF THE RECORD. Consistent with the Works' own stated
method, this declaration does not claim results beyond what the Works
themselves report. The light-field nucleation-bias hypothesis was
tested against real glycine NPLIN data and found negligible at
realistic conditions; the diamond CVD fabrication-time projection is a
proposed novel combination of independently published, confirmed
techniques, not a system that has been built or tested as an integrated
whole. This Article dedicates and protects the Works as they actually
are, not as they might be oversold to be.


========================================================================
              Article III -- The Grant
========================================================================

This License grants a single, unified right of use. There are no tiers.
Permission for an entity excluded under S 3.2 is granted, if at all,
solely and personally by the license holder, in writing, on a
case-by-case basis. It does not arise from payment, prior dealing,
usage, or implication.

S 3.1  ELIGIBLE USERS. The Works may be used, studied, modified, and
distributed, free of charge and without separate permission, only by:

  (a) natural persons, acting in their individual capacity; and
  (b) non-profit organizations duly registered or recognized as such
      under the law of their jurisdiction, acting in furtherance of
      their non-profit purpose.

S 3.2  EXCLUDED USERS. Any company, corporation, partnership, limited
liability company, or other for-profit commercial entity -- and any
person acting on behalf of such an entity, in that capacity -- is
FORBIDDEN from using the Works in any way, for any purpose, whether
commercial or non-commercial, UNLESS AND UNTIL the license holder grants
that specific, named entity permission in writing. There is no standard
fee, rate card, or automatic path to permission. Permission is at the
license holder's sole discretion and may be granted, withheld,
conditioned, or revoked as the license holder sees fit. Written
permission granted to one entity does not extend to any affiliate,
subsidiary, parent, successor, or other entity absent express terms
saying so.

S 3.3  ATTRIBUTION. Attribution to the license holder and the Work name
must be preserved in all copies and derivative works made by eligible
users under S 3.1, or by an excluded entity under a written permission
issued under S 3.2. The 75th Avenue License v3.0 and its issuance
number must also be cited, per the notice text in Article VI.

S 3.4  DERIVATIVE WORKS. Derivative works must be distributed under
this same License, and remain subject to the same eligibility
restriction of S 3.1-3.2. An eligible user may not sublicense,
relicense, or otherwise pass on rights to an excluded entity; a
permitted entity under S 3.2 may not pass on rights beyond what its
written permission expressly allows.

S 3.5  NAME AND MARK. The Work name and the license holder's name or
designation may not be used in any product, service, marketing, or
branding by any party -- eligible or permitted -- without the license
holder's separate written consent.


